As the number of COVID-19 cases continue to rise, the ANC's national working committee is said to be discussing a possible postponement of next year’s local government election. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - COVID-19 could impact next year's local government elections. The ANC's National Working Committee is discussing a possible postponement. ANC spokesperson Pule Mabe says the ANC NWC has reflected on a variety of options including synchronizing of national, provincial and local government elections. READ: Independent candidates can now contest general elections In March the IEC postponed by-elections due to the pandemic. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.